Pricing Maturity
Risk Alignment: State Farm emphasizes aligning pricing with risk, particularly in high-risk areas like California, where they have faced significant underwriting losses due to wildfires and other factors.
https://newsroom.statefarm.com/state-farm-general-insurance-company-update-on-california-2-2025/?
https://www.insurance.ca.gov/0400-news/0100-press-releases/2025/release018-2025.cfm?
 
Transition to More Sustainable Pricing
Rate Adjustments: State Farm has been seeking rate increases to stabilize its financial position, especially in California, where they have experienced substantial underwriting losses.
https://www.sfchronicle.com/california/article/state-farm-car-insurance-19964552.php? 

Digital Transformation in Pricing
Personalized Pricing Tools: State Farm offers the Personal Price Plan, which allows customers to personalize their insurance coverage, potentially leading to more efficient pricing processes.
https://www.statefarm.com/insurance/personal-price-plan?
 
Delegated Underwriting Authority
Agent Network: State Farm's extensive agent network plays a crucial role in underwriting and pricing by providing localized service and personalized policy adjustments.
https://www.autoinsurance.com/companies/state-farm/?

Future Outlook (2025-2026)
Regulatory Reforms: State Farm is looking forward to regulatory reforms that could allow for more dynamic pricing models, such as using forward-looking catastrophe models.
 https://www.carriermanagement.com/news/2025/03/02/272410.htm?
